  button(class='collapsible') POS-Tagging ▼
  div(class='technique-table')
    table
      tr
        th Definition
        th Example
      tr
        td A Part-Of-Speech Tagger (POS Tagger) is a piece of software that reads text in some language and assigns parts of speech to each word (and other token), such as noun, verb, adjective, etc., although generally computational applications use more fine-grained POS tags like 'noun-plural'. (Stanford Natural Language Processing Group)
        td #[a(href="https://medium.freecodecamp.org/an-introduction-to-part-of-speech-tagging-and-the-hidden-markov-model-953d45338f24") An introduction to part-of-speech tagging and the Hidden Markov Model]

