        th Example
      tr
        td Principal component analysis (PCA) is a technique used to emphasize variation and bring out strong patterns in a dataset. It's often used to make data easy to explore and visualize. (Setsoa.io)
        td #[a(href="http://setosa.io/ev/principal-component-analysis/") Principal Component Analysis Explained Visually]

