  div(class='technique-table')
    table
      tr
        th Definition
        th Example
      tr
        td An "emulator" is a software which mimics the behaviour of another computer environment. It is used in digital preservation to access software and digital files which require obsolete technological environments to run. (Oxford Libguides)
        td #[a(href="http://www.dlib.org/dlib/october00/granger/10granger.html") Emulation as a Digital Preservation Strategy]

